.SH NAME
dotty-git-done - Return to trunk, prune merged branches everywhere, fast-forward.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty git done [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Finish a piece of work and reset to a clean, current trunk:
.IP "  1." 5
Check out the trunk branch (main)
.IP "  2." 5
Fetch all remotes with --prune
.IP "  3." 5
Delete every local branch already merged into trunk (upstream/main when
 present, else origin/main), dropping it from any recorded stack
.IP "  4." 5
Delete every origin branch already merged into trunk
.IP "  5." 5
Fast-forward the local trunk branch to the remote

.PP
Any remaining stack that has diverged from trunk is reported; check it out
and run \fBdotty git sync\fR to rebase and re-sign it.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for done


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty git done
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-git(1)\fP
